  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-04-28",
    "date": "2021-07-06T17:16:01Z",
    "text": "First-Time Homebuyer Act of 2021\n\nThis bill modifies the first-time homebuyer tax credit. Specifically, it increases the allowable dollar amount of the credit from $8,000 to $15,000, revises the income formula for determining the maximum allowable credit amount, replaces the limitation on the credit based on purchase price (currently, $800,000) with a limitation based on area median purchase price, and revises rules relating to recapture of the credit and to members of the Armed Forces."
  },
